  "texts": [
    "Feeding loop invariants into verifiers.",
    "For evaluation of the generated invariants, we need to determine their validity and usefulness.",
    "To this end, we first of all need to feed them into some verifier.",
    "Interactive verifiers natively provide ways of feeding in such inputs.",
    "In an interactive verification run, a software engineer provides program annotations (e.g., invariants) and the verifier tries to prove that some given specifications are never violated 3.In this work, our goal is to evaluate the ability of large language models to support verifiers."
